  "title": "Senior/Lab Engineer (Manufacturing/East Region)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Implement chemical and physical testing methods and SOPs.</li>\n  <li>Lead new instrument setup, method development, and validation.</li>\n  <li>Plan testing capacity based on internal and external needs.</li>\n  <li>Investigate and report laboratory measurement deviations.</li>\n  <li>Prepare quarterly, monthly, and special analytical reports.</li>\n  <li>Support production troubleshooting with appropriate lab solutions.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate correlation and round-robin testing across sites.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Chemical Process, Applied Science, Chemistry, or Physics.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 2 years of lab experience in semiconductor or manufacturing environment.</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of analytical methods, especially trace metals analysis.</li>\n  <li>Familiar with GLP, ISO/IEC 17025, and MSA is an added advantage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>______________________________________________________</strong></p>\n<p><strong>HOW TO APPLY :</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Interested candidates, please submit your resume by clicking on “Quick Apply” or contact win@hkmsvs.com for more details.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Please provide following information in the resume for immediate processing</strong></p>\n<p><strong>1) Reasons for leaving current and/or last employment</strong></p>\n<p><strong>2) Last drawn and/or current salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>3) Expected salary</strong></p>\n<p><strong>4) Date of availability and/or Notice Period</strong></p>\n<p><strong>All applications will be treated in strictest confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Wee Wai Dan</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA License No : 03C5391</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EA Reg No : R22109628</strong></p>",
